        start_time: "7:00PM",
        end_time: "?",
        name: `Elevate 2026`,
        sort_time: "2026-04-18 19:00:00",
        end_time_formatted: "2026-04-18 23:59",
        detail: "The Fine Arts Center—Greenville County’s public high school for the creative, performing, and visual arts—proudly presents Elevate 2026, its fifth annual showcase at the Peace Center.\nFollowing an unforgettable evening celebrating our 50th Anniversary in the Concert Hall, we return to the Gunter Theatre to mark our 51st year with a bold and inspiring celebration of artistic excellence.\nElevate 2026 features breathtaking performances by our accomplished performing arts students, a curated exhibition of exceptional Visual Arts and Architecture student work in the Gunter Theatre Lobby, and the induction of distinguished alumni into the Fine Arts Center Hall of Fame. Together, these elements create an immersive experience that highlights both the legacy and the future of the arts.\nThis is your opportunity to be captivated by the next generation of artists—innovators, storytellers, and performers—emerging from South Carolina’s first arts high school.\nSponsored by the Fine Arts Center Partners, Elevate 2026 promises an evening that will inspire, energize, and remind audiences why the arts matter.",
